      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T03:25:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "do we want the generic (\u003dless useful) git-diff or a more concrete (\u003dmore useful) git-log that would give us a blamelist?\nnote that strictly speaking git-diff would work even for different repos and for two commits where neither of commits is a ancestor of another, b/c git-diff just diffs two trees.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "1380f894a3d9f317ed84054ea4ac9c52bd49893b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
