        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T03:25:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "is this the only case when we use DIFF?\nI feel like DIFF is a premature abstraction. IMO we should design abstractions when \n1) we have at least two clear cases\n2) we need to write code that must work for both but at the same time does not have to understand specifics of each case\nHere we have \n1) one case: git\n2) the code that would use DIFF (git log/diff) has to understand git concepts anyway. It can just check that repo url is the same",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 118,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 118,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "1380f894a3d9f317ed84054ea4ac9c52bd49893b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
